OL,3,CWhy does the deputy speaker oversee
OL,4,Cthe Budget rather than Sir Lindsay
OL,5,CHoyle?
OL,7,FAs Rachel Reeves presented her second
OL,8,FBudget to the House of Commons, it was
OL,9,FNusrat Ghani - not Sir Lindsay Hoyle -
OL,10,Fwho presided over the Chamber.
OL,12,FHoyle's absence from Budget statements
OL,13,Ffollows a long-standing parliamentary
OL,14,Fconvention: the speaker traditionally
OL,15,Fsteps back, leaving the session to be
OL,16,Foverseen by a deputy speaker,
OL,17,Fspecifically the chairman of Ways and
OL,18,FMeans.
